accessrestrict.head: Information about Access
accessrestrict.p: Series 2: Woodside Library Garden is open for research use. Materials are otherwise restricted for 75 years from date of creation.

bioghist.head: Biographical/Historical Sketch
bioghist.p: The Woodside-Atherton Garden Club was formally organized in 1929, and accepted into the Garden Club of America in 1934. The club organizes civic and educational projects, and hosts and participates in local and national flower shows.

scopecontent.head: Description of the Collection
scopecontent.p: Records consist primarily of meeting minutes, annual reports, news clippings, event programs, photograph albums and scrapbooks, and miscellaneous records of activities of the club from its inception forward. Photograph albums document various flower shows and local club efforts in the community.

acqinfo.head: Acquisition Information
acqinfo.p: This collection was given to the Stanford University Archives by the Woodside-Atherton Garden Club in June 2009, 2012, 2013
